.DT
verbose
Discworld player help
verbose

.SH Name
.SI 5
verbose - verbose mode control
.EI

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
verbose [type|all]
.EI

.SH Description

.SP 5 5
The verbose command controls which things you see in brief mode and which in verbose. Typing just 'verbose' will list which items are in which state. Typing 'verbose all' will set all items to verbose mode.

In verbose mode you will get longer descriptions of events depending on which items you have in verbose mode.
.EP

.SH Examples
> verbose
Your settings are: combat (verbose) look (brief) score (verbose) names (verbose)
> verbose look
Ok.
> verbose all
Ok.

See also
.SI 5
brief
.EI
